        <p><strong>Inline code:</strong> <code>&lt;div&gt;code&lt;/div&gt;</code></p>
        <p><data>data</data> can be used to markup machine-readable text.</p>
        <p>The <dfn>dfn element</dfn> indicates a definition.</p>
        <p>The <i>i element</i> is text that is offset from the normal text.</p>
        <p><em>This text has added emphasis.</em></p>
        <p>use <kbd>keyboard text</kbd> to indecate keystrokes</p>
        <p>The <mark>mark element</mark> indicates a highlight.</p>
        <p>
          <q cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/HTML/Element/q">
            This text is a short inline quotation.
          </q>
        </p>
        <p>
          This is example of Japanese text annotated with &lt;Ruby&gt; tags
          <ruby>
            <ruby>
              未<rp>(</rp><rt>み</rt><rp>)</rp>
              来<rp>(</rp><rt>らい</rt><rp>)</rp>
              .<rp>(</rp><rt>ドット</rt><rp>)</rp>
